job_description:
Job Description

Programmer - Data Analyst I

Are you a person with a knack for maintaining a high standard of data quality & accuracy? Are you interested in working in a multilingual, dynamic and friendly environment that encourages personal and professional development? We would love to meet you!

The Programmer – Data Analyst I is responsible for supporting the development, maintenance and monitoring of innovative solution and automated business processes. Working in a highly dynamic technical environment, this entry-level position contributes to the development and maintenance processes that support business operations. The role may also include monitoring, troubleshooting, and supporting business processes and integrations across platforms such as IBM Sterling B2B, Snowflake, Workday, Appian, and related systems. The incumbent will assist in delivering reliable data solutions, ensuring data quality, and supporting daily operational processes while developing technical and business knowledge. 

What does your typical day look like?

• Participate in the analysis, design and development of solutions in an effort to interface data or to drive business automations and decision making.
• Produce design documentation of the solution based on the requirements as defined by the requestor, business analyst and subject matter expert.
• Work closely with Business Analysts and other team members to both develop detailed specification documents with clear deliverables and timelines, and to ensure timely completion of deliverables.
• Communicate to team members with efficiency and accuracy any progress and/or delays. Engage in outside-the-box thinking to provide high value-of-service to clients.
• Develop and maintain SQL Stored Procedures that drive business through our core applications using SSMS.
• Develop and maintain SSIS and IBM Sterling B2B processes to drive file exchange with clients and Vendors.
• Develop and maintain reports that provide the business with operational data and analytics that influence decision making or business planning and auditing.
• Participate in daily application support meetings.
• Participate in the investigation related to product issues identified by the business or team members.
• Monitor business process activity with a focus on building resilience.
• Provide quick resolutions to issues in an effort to deliver effective customer service.

What skills and experience are we looking for?

• Bachelor’s degree in computer science or equivalent or equivalent with 1 to 3 years of related work experience;
• Working knowledge of ETL concepts.
• Familiarity with X12 (ANSI ASC X12) a widely used Electronic Data Interchange (EDI) standard.
• Intermediate-level knowledge and skill with SQL products (SSMS, SSIS, SSRS).
• Focused on service delivery and/or service oriented.
• Strong verbal and written communication skills (French and English);
• Strong analytical and problem-solving skills;
• Strong interpersonal skills;
• Team-oriented, adaptable, innovative thinker, flexible, and positive;
• Customer-service oriented.

When You Apply

If you require assistance or accommodation during our recruitment process, please notify Human Resources so that we can review and consider how we may be able to assist you based on your individual needs.

We offer you

• Global Excel offers more than a position;
• We offer a competitive compensation package that includes a base salary, performance bonus and an extensive benefits package;
• A professional future with opportunities for development, growth, and advancement;
• RRSP Match program;
• Financial assistance to employees who wish to continue their education;
• Work/life balance, health and wellness initiatives including an excellent EAP program;
• Employee engagement programs that focus on fitness, food, and fun;
• Windsor, Ontario Candidates: base hourly salary scale ($26.56/hour - $34.86/hour). Relevant candidate experience considered;
• Other locations, salary to be discussed based on geographic differential.
